<br>
<br>
  This adventure begins as I was spelunking in a cave off of paineel known to the local yokels as the hole.  We took a few people down there to cleanse the area of a ghost that was haunting the local people of paineel ( who the hell can scare those necrophiliacs ).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
  /ooc on, This was for Aavixx's SK epic, she did the turn in, and one ghost was supposed to spawn, but instead THREE spawned, we killed one, she looted, and then we got wiped out, /ooc off. <br>
<br>
  There were 3 ghosts, and we werent prepared for all of them, so I woke up in my home away from home, skyshrine.<br>
<br>
  I am a sneaky little bastard so it is a duty of mine to pull the dead out from under the noses of our enemies most of the time, and I was called upon to do this.  This was about 1 and a half RL hours after the fight with the ghost.  The slacker druid that was chosen to come get me hadnt persued velious ventures as far as wakening lands, or cobalt scar, so I had to meet her in the Not-so-great divide.<br>
<br>
I ran through the wakening lands, np, and then through kael.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well I am not a friend of the giants so I have to preform this jaunt through kael as silently as possible so as to not be seen or heard by the giants ( HOW THE HELL ARE THERE SO MANY GIANTS BUT NO WOMEN? ).<br>
<br>
<br>
As most of you probably know, Kael has its fair share of stairs.  As most of you short people probably know, these stairs are not designed for us.  Because I am shorter than the actual stair I have to jump up them instead of walking up them like the giants.  Jumping takes stamina, It takes me about a full bubble to clear 5 stairs.<br>
<br>
<br>
So I get to the stairs and I start jumping up them, I finally made it to the last one ( Segfault tells the guild, &quot;Huff Huff Pant Pant&quot;, Aavixx tells the guild, &quot;Bow chica bow wow&quot; ).  Well I made it up the stairs, and I started heading toward the eastern wastes.  I see Mr. Kromriff Recruiter and he tries to recruit me as a shoe cleaner for the Kromriff but I told him I had nothing to do with shoes as I am a halfling so I do not know how to clean them.<br>
<br>
There Is one more incline near the EW zone that us halflings have to jump over, so I ran up to it and jumped.<br>
<br>
<br>
You are too fatigued to jump.<br>
<br>
You are too fatigued to jump.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well I sit down so my stamina comes back.<br>
It doesnt come back.<br>
I get rdy to eat some jumjum.<br>
Doh, its on my corpse in the hole.<br>
<br>
